# Page Redesign — Mandatory Localization Gate

Every **page redesign** (Customer App `/app/*`, portals, embedded customer surfaces) ships **design + function + UX + full localization in one round**.

A page is **not complete** and **must not be locked** until localization passes.

## Scope — audit every customer-facing string

- Page titles, subtitles, eyebrows
- Navigation labels and tabs active on the page
- Buttons, links, CTAs
- Status labels (icon + text)
- Filters, forms, placeholders, tooltips
- Dialogs, confirmations
- Success / warning / error / empty / loading states
- Accessibility labels (`aria-*`, `sr-only`)
- Dynamic status mappings (enums → translated labels, never raw values)
- Date and number formatting via locale-aware formatters

## Languages — complete all active locales

Use the existing canonical architecture:

- Splits: `locales/{locale}/customer-app/*.json` via `getCustomerAppDictionaryForModule` / `getCustomerAppDictionaryForSplits`
- Label builders: `lib/**/labels.ts` — never hardcode copy in components
- **Core locales (mandatory):** `en`, `no`, `sv`, `da`, `pl`, `uk` — see [global-language-foundation.mdc](./global-language-foundation.mdc)
- English is fallback baseline; **other locales must not show English fallback text** in production UI

## Forbidden in production UI

- Hardcoded customer-facing strings in TSX
- Mixed-language pages (e.g. Norwegian nav + English panel headings)
- Visible translation keys (`customerApp.*`, raw key paths)
- Raw backend enums (`in_progress`, `critical_health`) shown to users
- Duplicate translation namespaces for the same page copy
- Norwegian-only fixes when other core locales are supported

## Verification before lock

1. `npm run validate:app-i18n` passes
2. No missing keys in any core locale for touched namespaces
3. Language switch works without reload/hydration errors
4. Desktop and mobile show the selected language consistently
5. Dynamic values use label lookup / semantic status system — not string concat of raw IDs

## Workflow

**Design → implement → i18n all locales → validate → then review/lock.**

Do not defer localization to a follow-up phase. Do not mark a page done after Norwegian-only pass.

See also [i18n-required.mdc](./i18n-required.mdc) and [global-language-foundation.mdc](./global-language-foundation.mdc).
